document object model

JavaScript can access all the elements in a webpage making use of Document Object Model (DOM). In fact, the web browser creates a DOM of the webpage when the page is loaded

html is used for structure the web page

css-is used for present the web page

javascript-add functionality(i.e behaviour) to the page

how does javascript interact with html and css

html program is converted into document object model using javascript virtual machine

javascript is access the html program though Dom

Each tag in the Dom is known as element node. Attribute is called as Attribute node and user text is called as text node

rectangle box is called as objects

